title: Fat Burning Cardio Low Impact Quiet Barefoot - Full 30-Minute Workout (Cardio Mat Fusion 2)
description:
GET OUR LOW IMPACT "WALK ON: 21 DAY WEIGHT LOSS PLAN" ON DVD: ‪http://amzn.to/1HVVgyp‬

GET THE DIGITAL DOWNLOAD: ‪http://bit.ly/1vEMf76‬

Cardio doesn't have to mean loud, joint jarring moves! Join certified instructor Jessica Smith for this non stop session that will keep your heart rate up (and your downstairs neighbors happy) and is gentle enough to be done barefoot (but you'll still work up a good sweat).

Oh, and Peanut the french bulldog makes an appearance in this video too :)

Level: All

Equipment: Mat

Intensity: Moderate

This workout targets the muscles in the thighs, back, calves, glutes, hamstrings, abs, core, hips, shoulders, arms, biceps, triceps, lower back (and more) with moves like:

Lateral Taps
Grand Plies
Side Lunges
Side Stretches
Side Oblique Crunch
Arm Circles
Side to Side Step Taps
Side Walking
Squats
Lateral Squats
Low Impact Skaters
Hamstring Curls
Plies
Figure-8 Lunges
Standing Saw
Passe Steps
Squat Reaches
Chair Pose
Twisted Chair
Prayer Pose
Plank Pose
Plank Running

Can Can Abs
Stretching

comments: Thank you for doing so many quiet workouts. I broke my pelvis four months ago and I can do most of your moves. I love being able to safely get my heart rate up! I used your sitting workout for the first few months of my recovery. You are awesome!
This channel has some of the most engaging, fun, and "feel good" workouts! Never stop doing what you're doing!

well this was my first ever workout with Jessica smith.  I do a lot of Ellen Barrett barefoot fusion workouts.  THis one I had sweat pouring off of me.  I thought I would not make it through.  But I did,  Look forward to doing more of her workouts.
oh boy, i thought i was ready to move on to your moderate intensity workouts...made it about half way and am drenched. Guess I'll stick with the beginners for a while longer! Thanks!

I paused the video for 30 seconds to caught breath and drink water every 12 minutes. I kept having to convince myself to keep going, but I did the whole thing and I feel good. I really needed a good sweat. I love that you have workouts for all fitness levels. Thank you for your hard work. You are so encouraging and realistic.
